The relative reactivity of the ROS/RNS under study was further analyzed by calculating their global chemical reactivity descriptors (GCRD), viz. global chemical hardness ( η ), global chemical potential ( μ ), electronegativity ( χ ), global electrophilicity ( ω ) and nucleophilicity ( N ) indices, in the gas phase and in aqueous solution, as given in Table 6 . These reactivity descriptors were calculated using the following relations: η =( E β LUMO - E α HOMO ), μ =( E α HOMO + E β LUMO )/2, χ =- μ, and ω = μ 2 /2 η (Domingo and Perez´, 2013;
;
). E α HOMO and E β LUMO represent the HOMO and LUMO energies of the α and β spin states of the reactive species, respectively. The global nucleophilicity ( N ) was calculated relative to the fluorine radical (Wu et al., 2017). The energies of the HOMO of the α spin states and LUMO of the β spin states of the considered ROS/RNS in the gas phase and aqueous solution are listed in Table S3 .

