DFT calculations were performed using the B3LYP three-parameter density functional (

; 

; Vosko et al., 1980). The geometries of all the structures were fully optimized at the B3LYP/6–311++G** level using the Gaussian 09W suite (Frisch et al., 2009). This was followed by harmonic frequency calculations to validate the stationary points and to account for the zero point energy corrections (

). The optimization of the reactive species was carried out using the unrestricted open shell (UB3LYP) approach at the same level of theory.

